Using instruction

Step 1

Plug the iphone 7 adapter into the lightning port of your iPhone/iPad.(The Cone logo faces you.)

Step 2

Connect the lightning cable and the headphones/aux cable to the iphone 7 adapter.
Then you can charge your device and play music.

Proper operation

Plug your headphone/cable into the 3.5mm aux port completely(Seamless) to make sure your music plays perfectly.

Wrong operation

It may cause something issue on the music function if you do not plug the headphone into the 3.5mm aux port completely.

Kellin Q
5.0 out of 5 starsNothing bad to say about these audio cables
July 23, 2017
Color: Does not Support iOS 10.3 and later-Gray|Verified Purchase
These have the same stepped design as my expensive V-Moda cable that came with my V-Moda M-100 headphones which is surprising for cheap cables like these. Tested against a good cable, with a Fiio E17k DAC/amp, as well with a good pair of headphones -- these sound just as good as my expensive cables and look great as well. Absolutely no background static and they seat fully into both audio jacks. I wasn't a huge fan of the red/orange colored cable that came with my headphones and these look a lot better. The length is better as well and is pretty much the perfect for having a phone in my pocket as my source for audio. Just enough excess cable to move freely but not so much that I need to stuff some in my pocket. The cable is braided so look up the pros and cons of that if you're unaware; some don't like braided cables because of their stiffness while others prefer them because of their strength and unwillingness to tangle.
